9. Rd1 {It's quite likely that you will get this position in one of your games via one or the other move order. Black has only made natural moves, but is already in great danger. The two best moves9...e5and9...Bd7are only played in a total of 25% of the games. Meanwhile, the two most popular moves,9...O-Oand9...Qc7, lead to a clearly better or even winning position for us.} 
9. O-O {After this most played move we already have a clear advantage or an approximate winning position.} 
10. e5 {Of course!} 
10. Ne8 {This is still the lesser evil. Black protects the d6-pawn one more time.} 
11. exd6
11. Nxd6 {This already loses a piece.} 
12. Bf4 {The knight cannot escape the pin and we attack it again with Nc3-e4 or Nc3-b5.} 
12. Qc7
13. Bxd6 {The most simple solution.} 
13. Bxd6
14. Nb5 {White wins a piece with the double attack on queen and bishop.} 
