7. g4 {Many beginners who are learning the principles of opening play are careful with such moves, as White's kingside is permanently weakened. However, we can certainly accept the weakening here, because the advantages clearly outweigh the disadvantages. We gain space on the kingside, push back the bishop and can fianchetto our bishop on g2. We're not obliged to castle short, but even if we do, the bishop protects our king and the push of the g-pawn doesn't matter that much.} 
