6. d5
7. Bd3 {Against the Petrov the bishop is usually most active on the d3-square.} 
7. Be7
8. O-O
8. O-O
9. h3 {By controlling the g4-square, we make the development of Black's queen's bishop more difficult. Next we bring the rest of the pieces into play and have a comfortable position.} 
