7. c5 {This is the most played move, but it's premature and simply loses the pawn on d6.} 
8. Ndb5 {That's exactly why we developed the bishop to f4.} 
8. Ne8 {This only delays the loss of the pawn.} 
9. O-O-O {By bringing our king to safety, we move the rook to d1, attacking the pawn on d6 again, which can no longer be defended.} 
