2. d6 {The Philidor Defense is the second most popular reply to 1. e4 at beginner level after 2...Nc6. Black protects the pawn on e5 and clears the way for the light-squared bishop. However, since the move does not fight for the center, we take the opportunity to occupy it.} 
3. d4
3. exd4
4. Nxd4 {We could also take back with the queen, but the knight is generally excellently placed in the center.} 
4. Nf6 {This is the most natural move. Black can also start with4...Be7,but he will not be able to do without the move ...Nf6 anyway.} 
5. Nc3 {We develop the knight and protect the e4-pawn.} 
5. Be7
6. Bf4 {This is the most ambitious setup. While it's only the sixth most popular move, it scores better than all other moves at a whopping 57%. Next we play Qd1-d2 and O-O-O.} 
