7. Nc6 {Black develops the knight, but since the move doesn't pose a threat, we can proceed with our plan.} 
8. O-O-O
8. Nxd4 {Black exchanges the knights, so that he can develop his light-squared bishop to e6.} 
9. Qxd4
9. Be6
10. f3 {We prepare a pawn storm on the kingside and have a clear plan: tear open the protection of the black king and checkmate!} 
