4. c3 {We are putting our development on hold for the moment as we want to build a strong center first. The push d2-d4 could now follow with gain of tempo, since the bishop on c5 would be attacked. Next we answer almost every black move with d2-d4.} 
4. a6 {After this or other harmless moves we reach our dream setup.} 
5. d4
5. exd4
6. cxd4
6. Ba7 {This is exactly why we played c2-c3. With the massive pawn center on e4 and d4 we control many important squares and have a significant space advantage.} 
7. O-O
7. d6
8. h3 {This preventive move makes sense in positions of this kind to prevent Bc8-g4.} 
8. Nf6
9. Nc3 {We develop our remaining pieces and have a fabulous position.} 
