16. O-O-O {This is probably the most logical continuation: Black brings the king to the queenside and protects the pawn on c7.} 
17. Bd6 {We use the pin on the c-file to provoke a weakening.} 
17. c6
18. a4 {Our dark-squared bishop has no opponent and Black's king is chronically weak. It will require a bit of technique, but we have excellent winning chances.} 
