14. Bxa1
15. Rxa1 {The knight on a5 will fall. Then we are already slightly ahead in terms of material (two minor pieces for rook and pawn). What matters much more, however, is the weakened dark squares around the opponent's king, which are almost begging for a mating attack. So we only need to place our queen on c3 or b2 and we are already threatening mate on g7. The position is clearly won for White.} 
