9. d5 {What a crazy move! We don't recapture the c3-bishop, but instead attack another piece, the c6-knight. The idea is to gain space and, above all, to prevent Black from playing the move d7-d5 to protect the knight on e4. Now, after d4-d5, not only is the knight on c6 attacked, a pin on the e4-knight on the e-file is also in the air.Black has two reasonable answers: either9...Ne5with a counterattack on the bishop on c4, or retreating the bishop with9...Bf6. But let's first examine the less good alternatives9...Na5and9...Ne7.} 
9. Na5 {Black puts the knight on the rim and attacks our bishop on c4. We skillfully move the bishop back one square and attack an opposing piece in turn.} 
10. Bd3 {Two black pieces are still under threat and we will get at least some of our material back. However, the knight on a5 stays out of the game for the time being and this is often the reason for our advantage.If you want to keep things even simpler, you can play10.bxc3Nxc4,which would transpose to the line 9... Ne5.} 
10. O-O
11. Bxe4 {We take the knight and Black has to do something about the attacked bishop on c3.11.bxc3is also a good try, when Black must find11...f5!⩲, as otherwise he is lost.11...f5is played in just under 6% of the games. However, after that it's not so easy for White to get through. The computer recommends another pawn sacrifice with12.d6.Feel free to take a look at it yourself if you are interested.} 
11. Bf6
12. Qc2 {We build a queen-bishop battery on the b1-h7 diagonal and threaten the pawn on h7. In addition, since the queen on c2 controls the c4-square, the black knight has no more squares and the typical push b2-b4 is in the air. However, we must first move the rook from a1, otherwise it could be taken by the bishop on f6.} 
12. h6
13. Rb1 {We evacuate the rook from the long a1-h8 diagonal and threaten to win the knight with b2-b4. If Black moves the b-pawn to clear b7 as a retreat square, we can think about d5-d6 attacking the rook on a8. Black is definitely under pressure and we're clearly better.} 
