9. Ne7 {After this relatively passive move, we recapture the bishop on c3 and then have nice compensation for the sacrificed pawn thanks to the space advantage and the bishop pair.} 
10. bxc3
10. Nxc3 {This is a terrible mistake.} 
11. Qd4 {We attack the knight on c3 and the pawn on g7. Black would be well advised to give up the knight and castle short, because if g7 falls, the black king gets stuck in the middle and doesn't survive the attack on the open e-file.} 
