12. Bg5 {We develop the bishop and want to exchange the important defender on f6. Since we threaten to take on f6 and weaken Black's pawn structure, he has to react.The move12.Rf4!?was played at the highest level; the idea is to sacrifice the exchange on f6. This looks exciting, but Black can play12...Ng6, after which we have nothing better than to repeat the moves with13.Re4+.} 
12. Bxg5
13. Nxg5
13. O-O {This isn't a mistake, but it can be quite dangerous for Black! He thinks he's safe after castling, but that's absolutely not true.} 
14. Nxh7 {We sacrifice the knight and then put our heavy pieces on the h-file. Now the cold sweat will break out on our opponent's forehead.} 
14. Bf5 {This counterattack is also possible.} 
15. Rh4
15. Bxh7
16. Qh5 {We threaten mate on h7 and the bishop can't move because of the mate on h8. We regain at least the bishop with an ongoing attack.} 
