17. Qh7+
17. Kf7
18. Rh6 {The rook controls important squares on the sixth rank and cannot be captured because the g7-pawn is pinned by the queen. We now have the devastating threat of Bc4-e2-h5+ and the king is running out of squares.} 
18. Rg8 {The only move. Black gives the king a retreat square on f8.} 
19. Re1 {We also bring the last piece into the attack!} 
19. Qf8 {Again, this is the only move to maintain balance.} 
20. Bb5 {A devilish move. We prevent Black from further development and threaten Re1-e6 followed by Rh6-f6 mate!By the way,20.Be2wouldn't work so well, since the king escapes with20...Ke8.} 
20. Rh8 {That's a very smart defense. The queen is deflected from pinning the g-pawn and then Black can capture our rook on h6.} 
21. Qxh8
21. gxh6
22. Qh7+ {We're not swapping queens as we're still down a piece.} 
22. Kf6
23. Rxe7 {This is important, because after other moves we are lost. Now we force a perpetual check.} 
23. Qxe7
24. Qxh6+
24. Kf7
25. Qh7+
25. Kf8
26. Qh8+
