3. c3 {We don't recapture the pawn with the queen, but attack it with the c-pawn. Now we threaten to take c3xd4 and build up a strong center, similar to the openings we play after 1. e4 e5. In over 70% of the games the Morra Gambit is accepted, which means that Black takes the pawn on c3. In this chapter, let's look at what happens if the gambit is declined.} 
3. Nf6 {This is my own recommendation (on Modern Chess) for Black's Sicilian repertoire. However, among beginners this move is only played in 4% of the games.} 
