4. Nd5
5. Nf3 {In the spirit of the Morra Gambit, we continue to offer the pawn on c3 in the next few moves. At the moment Black can't take it anyway. For instance,5...dxc3??drops the knight to6.Qxd5+-.} 
5. Nc6
6. Bc4 {We develop the bishop and attack the knight on d5.} 
6. Nb6 {6...e67.cxd4would transpose to the line 5... e6.} 
7. Bb3
7. d5 {Since we're capturing on d6 after this,7...d68.exd6would amount to the same thing.} 
8. exd6 {En passant!} 
8. Qxd6
9. O-O {Development comes first! We still don't care about recovering the d4-pawn.} 
9. dxc3 {That's exactly what we were waiting for.} 
10. Ng5 {Now let's launch a concrete attack!} 
10. Qxd1
11. Bxf7+ {A brilliant intermediate check!} 
11. Kd8
12. Rxd1+ {Next we take on c3 and have an excellent position.} 
