9. Qc7 {The most played move, but not a good choice (except for us!).For9...Nc6,see the mainline of 5...d6 and 6... e6.} 
10. Nb5 {This is our standard reaction if Black puts his queen on c7 without first playing a7-a6. We attack the queen and the already vulnerable d6-pawn at the same time.} 
10. Qc6
11. Nfd4 {We centralize the knight and attack the black queen again.} 
11. Qxe4
12. Nc7 {We win at least the exchange on a8 and have a clear material advantage.} 
