8. b3 {We reclaim the lost space!} 
8. cxb3
9. axb3 {We recapture towards the center, opening up the a-file for our rook.} 
9. O-O
10. c4 {We first leverage the center and then develop the knight to c3.} 
10. Nc6
11. Nc3 {Objectively the position is balanced, but I find it more comfortable to play for White. Black always has to take care of the d5-pawn and if he should capture on c4, we have full control over the center.} 
