1. d5 {The Scandinavian Defense is the fourth most popular opening at beginner level after 1...e5, Sicilian and French. Black occupies the center and wants to bring the strongest piece into play early on. However, this approach has the disadvantage that we can gain a tempo by attacking the queen. In addition, we can usually place our other central pawn on d4 and have a long-term space advantage. After studying the presented lines you will be happy if your opponent plays the Scandinavian.} 
