[Black "Scandinavian: 3...Qa5 #5"]
[FEN "rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4
1. d5 {The Scandinavian Defense is the fourth most popular opening at beginner level after 1...e5, Sicilian and French. Black occupies the center and wants to bring the strongest piece into play early on. However, this approach has the disadvantage that we can gain a tempo by attacking the queen. In addition, we can usually place our other central pawn on d4 and have a long-term space advantage. After studying the presented lines you will be happy if your opponent plays the Scandinavian.} 
2. exd5 {By taking the central pawn, we lure the black queen into the open where we can attack it.} 
2. Qxd5
3. Nc3 {We develop the knight, attack the black queen and force it to move again.} 
3. Qa5 {This is the most popular move. For now, the queen on a5 cannot be attacked, and after we move the d-pawn, our knight on c3 is pinned. However, that's no cause for concern.} 
4. d4 {We take the opportunity and occupy the center with our d-pawn.} 
4. Nf6
5. Nf3
5. c6
6. Bc4 {This is where the bishop is most active as it targets the pawn on f7.} 
6. Bg4 {6...Bf57.Ne5transposes to the line 5...Bf5 6. Ne5 c6.} 
7. h3 {Our reaction to the move ...Bg4 in the Scandinavian is always the same!} 
7. Bh5
8. g4 {We don't tolerate the knight being pinned for very long.} 
8. Bg6
9. Bd2 {Here the approach9.Ne5is not so convincing for a change, because Black has a strong reply in9...Nbd7!This clears the situation by forcing the exchange of our central knight.} 
9. Qc7 {As a precaution, Black removes the queen from the e1-a5 diagonal to avoid a possible discovered attack.} 
10. Qe2 {We finish our development and have an excellent position. Nf3-e5 and the advance of the h-pawn are in the air. Black should definitely keep his hands off the pawn on c2:} 
10. Bxc2
11. Ne5 {First we position the knight and attack the pawn on f7 a second time.} 
11. e6
12. Rc1 {And now we hunt down the bishop!} 
12. Bg6
13. h4 {Black either loses the bishop or suffers an enormous weakening of his structure. Either way, we're definitely going to win.} 
