6. c6 {This is a very typical move in the Pirc Defense. Black clears squares for the queen, controls the square on d5 and has the idea of the central push d6-d5 in mind.} 
7. Bd2 {7.Be3is also possible, but after7...d5things could get a little complicated in view of the threat Bf8-c5. On the other hand, if Black plays7...d5in the position after 7. Bd2, we castle long and everything in our position is defended. We're clearly better thanks to the space advantage.} 
